## âš ï¸ Contraindications & Cautions

**Treatment Contraindications:**
- Avoid tonifying herbs (like Ren Shen, Huang Qi) as they can trap the pathogen and worsen the condition.
- Avoid warming and acrid herbs (like Ma Huang in its raw form, Gui Zhi) as they will aggravate the Heat.

**Cautions:**
- The use of very cold and bitter herbs (e.g., Huang Qin, Huang Lian) should be moderated to avoid injuring the Spleen and Stomach Qi, which can lead to poor digestion or diarrhea.
- This is an excess pattern; treatment should focus on draining the excess, not tonifying.

